# Documentation

Path: `/srv/Inabiya/Docs/` (`docs` → `Docs` symlink for Cursor rules).

| Doc | Owns | Not for |
|---|---|---|
| `PRD.md` | Product behavior | Session progress |
| `Architecture.md` | Structure (Inabiya domains) | Education/LMS features |
| `Rules.md` | Engineering law | Live checkbox status |
| `Phases.md` | Delivery sequence | “What we finished today” |
| `Design.md` | Visual systems A/B | API contracts |
| `Memory.md` | Live progress, decisions, blockers | Full PRD paste |
| `IMPLEMENTATION_AUDIT.md` | Phases ↔ repo cross-check | Design tokens |
| `PORTS.md` | Inabiya port cheat-sheet | Global VPS registry (that’s `/srv/scripts/PORT_REGISTRY.md`) |

## Edit discipline

- Prefer **Memory** for progress; keep it dated, phase-tagged, secret-free, ≤5 next actions.
- Stack/sequence changes → sync `Rules.md` / `Phases.md` (and Cursor rules if agent behavior must change).
- Architecture may still mention LMS residue — **never reintroduce** Student/Admission/Hostel into Inabiya docs or code.
- Mark decisions with date + rationale; don’t silently rewrite history.
- Surgical edits unless the user asked for a rewrite.
- After meaningful implementation: update Memory checkboxes + session log (core protocol).
